cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.ST, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a novel computational framework for Bayesian inference with regularization, which is relevant to several subfields in computer science. The use of nonparametric Bayesian methods and large-margin learning suggests that the paper may belong to the subcategories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The information theoretical formulation of the regularization term may also make the paper relevant to the subcategory of information theory (cs.IT). The empirical studies on benchmark datasets suggest that the paper may belong to the subcategories of statistics (cs.ST) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
